HEADWORD: Eye-splice
<hw>Eye"-splice`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>A splice formed by bending a rope's end back, and fastening it into
the rope, forming a loop or eye. See <xex>Illust.</xex> under
<er>Splice</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

